value: Breeds on the New Siberian Islands and on the Arctic coast of Siberia from the Yana River to Bering Strait and on the Alaskan coasts from Kuskokwim River to Barter Island. Winters in the Aleutian Islands.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Arctic ponds, lakes, deltas, and tidal inlets with grass or sedge margins; in winter, primarily openings in pack ice.
br coastal tundra, inland coastal waters, also far offshore

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip
